2/4/99
    To support PTS/DTS recovery: (all done)
        - Add the PTS/DTS recovery module.
        - Have switcherTask filter any on/off channel pictures with pending
          PTS/DTS without delivering it to the state machine.
        - Modify the state machine so that it will loop on master channel
          also. 


2/5/99
    Fixed the hanging bug: in the SPLICE mode, after entry point in the off
    stream is found, the exit point in the on stream needs to be found.
    In this case, we should release the DTS lock.  Otherwise we may not be
    able to find the exit point.
    
    Need to debug the time stamp recovery module. (on going)

    Need to improve acquisition time by allowing parallel detection of
      PCR/DTS and sequence header.
   
    Bug: for PTS update, cannot simply update the first picture in queue,
         since there may be some pending B picture in the front due to
         DTS locking! 
    Solution: change pendingPts flag to a pointer to the picture with
              pending PTS.  Pointer will be 0 if there is no such picture.

    Time stamp recovery seems to be working now.  Switch in an out works when:
        All PTS/DTS of anchor pictures (both channel) are removed, and
        all PTS of B pictures (both channel) are removed.
    Need to check more closely though.


